statements.sql: select `product_id`, `status` from `ec_bookings` right join `ec_orders` on `ec_bookings`.`order_id` = `ec_orders`.`id` where `PickingUpDate` <= 1675720800 and `DroppingOffDate` >= 1675720800 and `status` = 'completed'

select count(*) as aggregate from `ec_products` left join
(
SELECT ec_season.cost,
ec_season.base_price,
ec_season.product_id
FROM ec_season
WHERE
ec_season.startDate <= '1688311870' and ec_season.endDate >= '1688311870'
and  ec_season.Duration = (
SELECT MAX(s2.Duration)
FROM ec_season s2
WHERE
s2.startDate <= '1688311870' and s2.endDate >= '1688311870'
and  s2.Duration <=  1  AND
s2.product_id = ec_season.product_id )
)
AS t1 on `t1`.`product_id` = `ec_products`.`id` where `published_at` is not null and `published_at` < '2023-07-02 18:31:10' and `ec_products`.`deleted_at` is null

select *, COALESCE(t1.cost, t1.base_price, `ec_products`.`price`) AS final_cost from `ec_products` left join
(
SELECT ec_season.cost,
ec_season.base_price,
ec_season.product_id
FROM ec_season
WHERE
ec_season.startDate <= '1688311870' and ec_season.endDate >= '1688311870'
and  ec_season.Duration = (
SELECT MAX(s2.Duration)
FROM ec_season s2
WHERE
s2.startDate <= '1688311870' and s2.endDate >= '1688311870'
and  s2.Duration <=  1  AND
s2.product_id = ec_season.product_id )
)
AS t1 on `t1`.`product_id` = `ec_products`.`id` where `published_at` is not null and `published_at` < '2023-07-02 18:31:10' and `ec_products`.`deleted_at` is null order by `final_cost` asc, `price` asc limit 7 offset 0
